cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use or discuss this software, cite the exact release tag or commit."
title: "ECL: Closure-Aware Event Certification Framework"
type: software
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: 2026-07-15
authors:
  - family-names: "Dabas"
    given-names: "Monty"
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0005-6948-209X"
    affiliation: "Independent Researcher"
abstract: >-
  A bounded public research package for deterministic closure-aware event
  certification, seam-rupture analysis, phase-lock measurement, winding and
  orientation consistency, residue-aware ledgers, explicit thresholds, and
  machine-readable certificates. Version 1.0.0 stabilizes the public command
  and certificate interface. Passing repository tests does not by itself
  establish a universal mathematical law, physical mechanism, cryptographic
  security, legal priority, or production readiness.
keywords:
  - event certification
  - closure audit
  - seam rupture
  - phase locking
  - winding number
  - reproducible research
  - research certificates
repository-code: "https://github.com/Parveen117/ECL-public"
